verbs.description: upthunder (third-person singular simple present upthunders, present participle upthundering, simple past and past participle upthundered)

entries.meaning: (poetic, archaic, intransitive) To send up a noise like thunder.
examples: Strange-eyed Destruction! who with many a dreamOf central fires through nether seas — upthunderingSoothes her fierce solitude.
